data.description: Motivated Sellers! Location, location, location! Welcome Home to this advantageous 4-bedroom 2.5 bath home, that has everything you need!  Situated on a substantial corner lot in the highly sought after The Landings Subdivision, which has no HOA. Enjoy the convenience of Peachtree City living, including golf cart path access, while paying lower property taxes for the city of Fayetteville! This home has much to offer and has been well maintained by its Original Owners! You'll love the abundance of living space on the main floor with 2-story foyer entrance. From the large family room with fireplace, to the keeping room/flex space, the beautiful dining room, and half bath. You’ll find Hunter Douglas Programmable Blinds in the Dining & Living Rooms. The kitchen has been updated with granite counter tops, chefs island, and office nook with large pantry. Just off the kitchen is additional space that would be wonderful to curl up with a book with optimal lighting from all the windows situated at your covered and screened in porch. Enjoy sitting and watching the game while grilling out! Just off the screened in porch is a large deck that leads to a gas firepit (gas is ran from the home!) The yard boasts an immaculately kept Emerald Zoysia lawn with additional mature landscaping. Sprinkler System & Drip Irrigation which features the Sprinkler Magician. A fully automated sprinkler system that takes care of your entire yard from pest control to fertilization. At night enjoy favorably situated landscape lighting that truly brings a beautiful glow to the home. After a long day, if are you not feeling a trip up the stairs? No worries! This home comes with its very own ELEVATOR! Built completely up to code and ready to assist you to your primary suite! Once you exit the elevator you're met with an oversized primary suite with trey ceilings, walk in closet, large bathroom with cathedral ceilings, double vanity, jetted garden tub, and walk in shower! Situated on the 2nd floor is 3 additional bedrooms, a full bathroom, and laundry room! Mentionable bathroom updates include; toilets, tile, & cabinetry. The basement is partially finished with heating and air. It even has its very own fireplace! The basement could easily be converted into a mother-in-law suite with space for a bathroom. It has ground level entrance, natural lighting from windows,  and ample storage space! Updated A/C units and newer architectural shingled roof.  The 3 Car Garage has additional attic space. The 3rd garage is separated and would make an ideal workshop/space. It's also perfect for storing your golf cart when you explore the 100+ miles of PTC golf cart paths! Seller open to negotiations and sellers concessions with agreeable offer!
